I’ve isolated the core logic. The router has almost no internal state, so the main attack surface is not bookkeeping bugs in storage; it’s whether the router’s generic execution model lets untrusted callers misuse approved plugins or sweep incidental balances. I’m checking those boundaries and the balance invariant carefully now.
